0with%20parents%20who%20understood%20my%20experience.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20my%20daughter%20was%20born%2C%20I%20carefully%20laid%20the%20groundwork%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-parents-overwhelmed-advice-doubting-their-instincts-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esupport%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20everyone%20told%20me%20I%20would%20need%20as%20a%20new%20Mom%2C%20especially%20one%20living%20far%20from%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20to%20heart%20the%20advice%20that%20I%20would%20need%20a%20village%20to%20make%20it%20through%20the%20early%20years%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-not-want-children-now-mom-of-twelve-kids-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enavigating%20motherhood%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20my%20child%20to%20be%20surrounded%20by%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20when%20my%20daughter%20was%20born%20with%20disabilities%20and%20complex%20medical%20needs%2C%20my%20village%20vanished%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20create%20a%20new%20one%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228dbd614f-0888-4fd0-87cf-8f43dcd8078f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20worked%20hard%20to%20meet%20other%20first-time%20moms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20soon%20as%20I%20found%20out%20I%20was%20pregnant%2C%20I%20joined%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-goes-down-fear-as-mom-of-child-health-conditions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eonline%20groups%20for%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20were%20due%20around%20the%20same%20time%20as%20me.%20I%20signed%20up%20for%20prenatal%20yoga%20classes%20because%20I%20enjoyed%20the%20gentle%20stretches%20that%20eased%20my%20aches%20and%20pains.%20However%2C%20I%20kept%20going%20back%20because%20I%20enjoyed%20the%20company%20of%20other%20women%20who%2C%20like%20me%2C%20were%20pregnant%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20In%20my%20natural%20birth%20class%2C%20I%20constantly%20arranged%20(decaf)%20coffee%20dates%20and%20offered%20rides%20to%20other%20moms-to-be%20who%20wanted%20to%20look%20at%20cribs%20and%20bouncers%20at%20suburban%20big-box%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-are-the-symptoms-of-pregnancy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enavigating%20pregnancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20newly%20found%20group%20of%20expecting%20mothers.%20Together%2C%20we%20navigated%20prenatal%20woes%20like%20the%20dreaded%20glucose%20test%20and%20celebrated%20joys%2C%20like%20settling%20on%20the%20perfect%20baby%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20close%20to%20several%20of%20these%20women.%20We%20vowed%20to%20support%20each%20other%20by%20cooking%20meals%20for%20one%20another%20after%20delivery.%20We%20vowed%20to%20get%20together%20at%20least%20a%20couple%20of%20times%20a%20week%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-around-the-world-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ematernity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Someone%20suggested%20creating%20a%20babysitting%20co-op%20once%20our%20newborns%20were%20a%20few%20months%20old%2C%20and%20I%20was%20all%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7ab1c19-cb73-443d-b499-e773ef68d2f1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20daughter%20was%20born%20with%20disabilities%20and%20complex%20medical%20needs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20picture-perfect%20pregnancy%2C%20everything%20changed.%20My%20daughter%20was%20born%20disabled%20and%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flike-stauffer-family-i-considered-rehoming-my-child-with-autism-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecomplex%20medical%20needs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20spent%20weeks%20in%20the%20NICU%20while%20I%20pumped%20milk%20for%20her%20round-the-clock%20and%20slept%20on%20uncomfortable%20hospital%20fold-out%20chairs%20made%20out%20of%20vinyl%20that%20stuck%20to%20my%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20days%2C%20I%20forgot%20to%20eat.%20I%20didn't%20know%20whether%20my%20daughter%20would%20live%20or%20die%2C%20or%20what%20kind%20of%20life%20she%20would%20live%20if%20she%20ever%20saw%20the%20world%20outside%20her%20hospital%20room.%20When%20it%20came%20time%20to%20give%20my%20daughter%20a%20Hebrew%20name%2C%20I%20chose%20%26quot%3BChaya%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20%26quot%3Blife%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bto%20be%20strong.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20willing%20her%20to%20pull%20through%2C%20but%20I%20seemed%20to%20be%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3f8fea9-9979-4f59-89ae-319c3c8cdb23%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20daughter%20survived%2C%20but%20my%20village%20disappeared%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20survived%20those%20fraught%20few%20weeks.%20Eventually%2C%20she%20went%20home%2C%20albeit%20with%20monitors%20and%20oxygen%20tanks%20instead%20of%20teddy%20bears%20and%20soft%20blankets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20moms%20I%20had%20thought%20would%20be%20my%20support%20system%2C%20knowing%20I%20would%20be%20there%20for%20any%20one%20of%20them%20if%20they%20needed%20me.%20I%20discovered%20that%20the%20moms%20in%20the%20group%20that%20formed%20when%20we%20were%20pregnant%20had%20indeed%20been%20getting%20together%20as%20planned.%20They%20didn't%20want%20to%20bother%20me%2C%20they%20said%2C%20so%20they%20hadn't%20reached%20out.%20They%20assumed%20I%20needed%20my%20space%2C%20they%20told%20me%2C%20when%20what%20I%20really%20needed%20was%20their%20friendship%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20wondered%20if%20I%20was%20their%20worst%20nightmare%2C%20a%20Mom%20with%20a%20sick%20and%20disabled%20baby%20who%20made%20problems%20with%20sleep%20regression%20seem%20like%20child's%20play.%20Their%20reaction%20made%20sense.%20Throughout%20our%20pregnancies%2C%20all%20we%20ever%20heard%20was%20that%20if%20our%20babies%20were%20born%20healthy%2C%20everything%20else%20would%20be%20OK.%20Now%20that%20one%20of%20us%20had%20a%20baby%20that%20had%20not%20been%20born%20healthy%2C%20there%20was%20no%20road%20