triot%20air%20defense%20system%2C%20but%20officials%20say%20more%20must%20be%20done.%3Cp%3EPeter%20Mueller%2FBundeswehr%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENATO%20members%20often%20aren't%20buying%20weaponry%20together%2C%20an%20alliance%20official%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20shared%20that%20nations%20still%20approach%20industry%20%26quot%3Bindividually%20with%20their%20individual%20requirements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20also%20said%20NATO%20needs%20to%20change%20its%20development%20models.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20members%20aren't%20regularly%20buying%20weapons%20together%2C%20limiting%20how%20quickly%20and%20cheaply%20they%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-promise-air-defense-spending-money-alone-wont-solve-issue-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuild%20up%20stockpiles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20senior%20alliance%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarja%20Jaakola%2C%20NATO's%20assistant%20secretary%20general%20for%20defense%20industry%2C%20innovation%2C%20and%20armaments%2C%20said%20that%20allies%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-shows-nato-buys-and-builds-weapons-wrong-official-says-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eacquire%20weaponry%3C%2Fa%3E%20most%20cost-effectively%20by%20jointly%20purchasing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20multiple%20countries%20trying%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ramping-up-production-of-weapons-critical-for-major-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eindependently%20develop%20similar%20weaponry%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20fewer%20resources%20per%20program%20and%20higher%20per-unit%20costs%20than%20working%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20said%20that's%20often%20not%20what%20is%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20talk%20with%20the%20industry%2C%20the%20industry%20keeps%20telling%20me%20many%20nations%20still%20approach%20them%20individually%20with%20their%20individual%20requirements.%20And%20that%20is%20something%20that%20we%20should%20avoid%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20UK%20think%20tank%20Chatham%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20should%20look%20at%20how%20much%20can%20we%20collaborate%2C%20work%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaakola%20said.%20She%20said%20shared%20systems%20also%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20allies%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-teaching-nato-air-forces-lessons-fighting-russia-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoperate%20together%20in%20a%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20countries%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20sure%20that%20we%20use%20the%20taxpayer's%20money%20cost%20efficiently%2C%26quot%3B%20especially%20given%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20cost%20escalation%20within%20defense%20systems%20is%20higher%20than%20in%20the%20civilian%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20allies%20should%20be%20embracing%20collaboration%2C%20co-production%2C%20and%20joint%20procurement%3A%20developing%2C%20building%2C%20and%20buying%20weapons%20together.%20NATO%20is%20made%20up%20of%2032%20countries%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20small.%20Internal%20competition%20for%20resources%20and%20contracts%20isn't%20desirable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvasion%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20driven%20worries%20of%20wider%20war%20across%20the%20alliance%20and%20a%20flurry%20of%20defense%20spending.%20As%20more%20money%20flows%20into%20defense%2C%20questions%20are%20being%20raised%20about%20traditional%20development%20and%20acquisition%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20traditional%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-weapon-making-issue-highlighted-ukraine-being-faster-denmark-pm-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edefense%20development%20cycles%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20too%20slow%2C%20and%20the%20resulting%20arsenals%20are%20too%20small.%20Ukraine%20is%20demonstrating%20that%20it%20can%20build%20and%20modify%20weapons%20more%20quickly%20and%20cheaply%20than%20its%20partners%20typically%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20across%20the%20alliance%20have%20noted%20the%20issue%20and%20advocated%20for%20joint%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20has%20been%20increasingly%20pushing%20for%20greater%20joint%20production%20and%20encouraging%20allies%20to%20take%20out%20multinational%20contracts.%20The%20alliance%20said%20last%20year%20that%20member%20states%20are%20invited%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20joint%20procurement%20the%20preferred%20procurement%20choice.%26quot%3B%20The%20European%20Union%2C%20where%20most%20of%20NATO's%20members%20are%20based%2C%20has%20also%20changed%20rules%20to%20incentivize%20joint%20procurements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20Secretary%20General%20Mark%20Rutte%20said%20that%20joint%20procurement%20should%20reduce%20costs%20for%20alliance%20members%20when%20buying%20gear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20leaders%20in%20Europe%20feel%20the%20same.%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20European%20Commission%2C%20said%20last%20year%20that%20joint%20procurement%20would%20%26quot%3Breduce%20costs%2C%20reduce%20fragmentation%2C%20increase%20interoperability%2C%20and%20strengthen%20our%20defence%20industrial%20base.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20living%20in%20the%20most%20momentous%20and%20dangerous%20of%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20warned.%20%26quot%3BThe%20real%20question%20in%20front%20of%20us%20is%20whether%20Europe%20is%20prepared%20to%20act%20as%20decisively%20as%20the%20situation%20dictates.%20And%20whether%20Europe%20is%20ready%20and%20able%20to%20act%20with%20the%20speed%20and%20the%20ambition%20that%20is%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaakola%20said%20that%20one%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%20example%26quot%3B%20of%20effective%20joint%20production%20is%20the%20interceptor%20missiles%20for%20the%20US%20MIM-104%20Patriot%20air%20defense%20system.%20There%20is%20increasing%20co-production%20for%20them%2C%20including%20Germany's%20establishment%20of%20facilities%20to%20produce%20missiles%20there.%20But%20her%20comments%20suggest%20there%20is%20much%20more%20to%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20briefing%20presented%20last%20year%20to%20European%20Parliament%20members%20revealed%20that%20joint%20procurement%20across%20the%20union%20was%20far%20below%20targets%2C%20even%20though%20it%20said%20doing%20so%20would%20allow%20for%20better%20industrial%20leverage%2C%20better%20interoperability%2C%20and%20annual%20savings%20of%20several%20billion%20euros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaakola%20also%20said%20that%20NATO%20militaries%20need%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeed-ukraine-battlefield-development-pushes-weapons-makers-modular-software-first-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echange%20how%20they%20develop%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20said%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20how%20weapons%20can%20be%20developed%20and%20fielded%20far%20faster%20than%20in%20NATO%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it's%20an%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20lesson%20that%20we%20need%20to%20learn%20from%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20NATO%20needs%20to%20%26quot%3Bactually%20see%20how%20we%20can%20change%20our%20own%20mindset%20and%20our%20own%20way%20of%20working%20when%20we%20talk%20about%20capability%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-allies-arent-buying-enough-weaponry-together-official-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774782721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c67e1546a3e043bdfc5bce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-allies-arent-buying-enough-weaponry-together-official-2026-3%22%2C%22summa